title: [JIT] Don't support enumerate in the Script
body_html:
As of now we could not support enumerate in script:

RuntimeError:
undefined value enumerate:
@torch.jit.script
def test():
    my_list = [3, 4, 5, 6]
    counter_list = list(enumerate(my_list, 1))
                        ~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE

If we use it in for:

NotSupportedError: the only expressions allowed on the left hand side of assignments are variable names and starred expressions
@torch.jit.script
def test():
    my_list = [3, 4, 5, 6]
    for counter, value in enumerate(my_list):
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE
        print(count, value)
body:
As of now we could not support enumerate in script:
```
RuntimeError:
undefined value enumerate:
@torch.jit.script
def test():
    my_list = [3, 4, 5, 6]
    counter_list = list(enumerate(my_list, 1))
                        ~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE
```

If we use it in for:
```
NotSupportedError: the only expressions allowed on the left hand side of assignments are variable names and starred expressions
@torch.jit.script
def test():
    my_list = [3, 4, 5, 6]
    for counter, value in enumerate(my_list):
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE
        print(count, value)
```
